<% content_for :title, "Walkthrough — the setup" %>

<section class="walkthrough">
  <%= render "progress" %>

  <h1>Try to commit fraud. Watch the gate refuse.</h1>

  <p>
    Payroll runs need two people: one <b>prepares</b> the run, a different person
    <b>approves</b> it. That is separation of duties — and it is not a policy you
    can switch off. Over the next three steps you will try to approve a run you
    prepared yourself, in every way the system allows, and be refused each time
    with an explanation.
  </p>

  <p>
    Start by stepping into the <b>preparer</b>. The banner at the top will name
    who you are acting as.
  </p>

  <p class="wt-actions">
    <%= button_to "Act as the preparer", act_as_path(id: @preparer.id),
          method: :post, class: "button--primary" %>
    <%= link_to "Next: see the run you prepared →", walkthrough_path(step: "prepared"),
          class: "button" %>
  </p>
</section>
